In a preliminary experiment, a solution containing $0.0837 \mathrm{M} \mathrm{X}$ and $0.0666 \mathrm{M} \mathrm{S}$ gave peak areas of $A_{\mathrm{X}}=423$ and $A_{\mathrm{S}}=347$. (Areas are measured in arbitrary units by the instrument's computer.) To analyze the unknown, $10.0 \mathrm{~mL}$ of $0.146 \mathrm{M} \mathrm{S}$ were added to $10.0 \mathrm{~mL}$ of unknown, and the mixture was diluted to $25.0 \mathrm{~mL}$ in a volumetric flask. This mixture gave the chromatogram in Figure 5-9, for which $A_{\mathrm{X}}=553$ and $A_{\mathrm{S}}=582$. Find the concentration of $\mathrm{X}$ in the unknown.【analysis】The content of this question is to use an internal standard.
【answer】step1:First use the standard mixture to find the response factor in Equation 5-11:

Standard mixture:$\frac{A_{\mathrm{X}}}{[\mathrm{X}]}=F\left(\frac{A_{\mathrm{S}}}{[\mathrm{S}]}\right) \\
& \frac{423}{0.0837}=F\left(\frac{347}{0.0666}\right) \Rightarrow F=0.970_{0}$

step2:In the mixture of unknown plus standard, the concentration of $\mathrm{S}$ is

$\text { [S] }=\underbrace{(0.146 \mathrm{M})}_{\begin{array}{c}
\text { Initial } \\
\text { concentration }
\end{array}} \underbrace{\left(\frac{10.0}{25.0}\right)}_{\begin{array}{c}
\text { Dilution } \\
\text { factor }
\end{array}}=0.0584 \mathrm{M}$

step3:Using the known response factor, substitute back into Equation 5-11 to find the concentration of unknown in the mixture:

$\begin{gathered}
\text { Unknown mixture: } \quad \frac{A_{\mathrm{X}}}{[\mathrm{X}]}=F\left(\frac{A_{\mathrm{S}}}{[\mathrm{S}]}\right) \\
\frac{553}{[\mathrm{X}]}=0.970_{0}\left(\frac{582}{0.0584}\right) \Rightarrow[\mathrm{X}]=0.0572{ }_{1} \mathrm{M}
\end{gathered}$

step4:Because $\mathrm{X}$ was diluted from 10.0 to $25.0 \mathrm{~mL}$ when the mixture with $\mathrm{S}$ was prepared, the original concentration of $\mathrm{X}$ in the unknown was $(25.0 \mathrm{~mL} / 10.0 \mathrm{~mL})\left(0.057 \quad 2_{1} \mathrm{M}\right)$ $=0.143 \mathrm{M}$.
【In summary,the original concentration of $\mathrm{X}$ in the unknown was $0.143 \mathrm{M}$.】

Write the mass balance for a saturated solution of the slightly soluble salt $Ag_3PO_4$, which produces $\mathrm{PO}_{4}^{3-}$ and $3\mathrm{Ag}^{+}$ when it dissolves.The mass balance for a saturated solution of the slightly soluble salt $Ag_3PO_4$ can be written as:

$$
\begin{aligned}
